name: Eógobal

attributes.attribute: father (or perhaps grandfather) of two goddesses or Fairy Queens of the southwestern province of Munster
not raised by Eógabal but by the sea god Manannán Mac Lir

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Irish mythology mentions the deity Eógobal, who is the probable father or grandfather of the two Fairy Queens or goddesses of Munster Province named Áine and Grian. Interestingly, Eógobal did not raise the two daughters, as they were brought up by the sea god named Manannán Mac Lir.
